RBS May Lend Up to $3 Billion to Shipping in 2011, List Says

-- B y   A l i s t a i r   H o l l o w a y
-- 
2011-02-28T11:12:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-28/rbs-may-lend-up-to-3-billion-to-shipping-in-2011-list-says.html
  Royal Bank of Scotland Group Plc  may
make up to $3 billion in new loans to the shipping industry this
year, up from $2.5 billion in 2010,  Lloyd’s List  reported,
citing comments from the bank’s global head of shipping, Lambros Varnavides.  The bank’s total ship lending stands at about $22 billion,
the newspaper said. Shamira Alidina, an RBS spokeswoman,
confirmed the figures to Bloomberg News by phone today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alistair Holloway in London at 
 aholloway1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
